<H3> <TI>   Company Expects Income Increase in 1994 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Company Expects Income Increase in 1994 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1705175294 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PA1705175294 </F>
<F P=104>  -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish at 0122 
GMT on 13 May reports that Cesar Gonzalez, manager of Veracuba 
Company, which is a branch of the Cubanacan, S.A. tourism group, 
says Veracuba's income is expected to increase by 20 percent 
from over $13 million in 1993 to $17 million in 1994. Veracuba, 
he explained, is involved in three activities: bus services, 
vehicle rentals and taxi services; and its purpose is to broaden 
Cubanacan's commercial activities. 

</TEXT>

