<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romanian Premier Arrives on Last Leg of Tour </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romanian Premier Arrives on Last Leg of Tour </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905155994 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1018 GMT 19 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asuncion ROMPRES 18/5/1994 -- Paraguay's capital 
Asuncion is the last stage of the South-American journey of 
Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu and his delegation, a 
stage that started on 18 May afternoon. The Romanian premier 
was welcomed at the airport by President Juan Carlos Wasmosy. 
The visit started with an interview between the Romanian 
premier and the Paraguayan president. Virtually, there is no 
tradition of Romanian-Paraguayan relations. Diplomatic 
relations were established only in 1992. The Romanian party 
considers that actions should be started soon, to secure a 
development of these relations. Priorities are the realization 
of adequate diplomatic representation in the two capitals, the 
conclusion of the first inter-government agreements, the 
development of trade. 
  The Paraguayan party has already shown interest in the 
domain 
of economic cooperation, in the building of a Romanian car 
assembly line, the building of cotton spinning mills, of 
electricity transport lines, oil and mining units. Trade and 
economic cooperation agreements and an agreement on mutual 
promotion and protection of investments are expected to be 
signed during Premier Vacaroiu's visit. 

</TEXT>

