<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romania's Vacaroiu Signs Cooperation Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romania's Vacaroiu Signs Cooperation Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1705185494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1109 GMT 17 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1705185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 17/5/1994 -- Several cooperation 
agreements were signed on Monday [16 May] between Romania and 
Peru occasioned by the visit paid by Romanian Prime Minister 
Nicolae Vacaroiu, currently on a Latin American tour. 
  Viewed by Premier Vacaroiu as the most significant, the 
agreement on trade and economic cooperation (signed by Minister 
of Trade Cristian Ionescu, on behalf of Romania, and by Liliana 
Canale, the Peruvian minister of industries, tourism, 
integration and international trade negotiations) stipulates the 
principles for trade operations based on market economy rules. 
  The Romanian premier and his Peruvian counterpart Efrain 
Goldenberg, who is also Peru's foreign minister, sealed an 
agreement for investment mutual guarantee and protection. 
  The third document -- the collaboration agreement between 
the 
National Agricultural University "La Molina" in Peru and the 
Bucharest Agricultural University -- was signed by Education 
Minister Liviu Maior on Romania's behalf and by Jose Dance 
Caballero, rector of the Peruvian institution. 
  Also sealed were two understandings by an exchange of 
letters 
signed by the two countries' foreign ministers, one setting up a 
mechanism of consultation between the two ministers, and another 
for free diplomatic, special and service visas. 
  Before the signing ceremony, Romanian Premier Nicolae 
Vacaroiu and his Peruvian counterpart, Efrain Goldenberg (whose 
parents are Bessarabian natives), had an interview during which 
stress was laid on "the extremely fine ties" between Romania and 
Peru. 
  Also on Monday, another agreement was signed by Aurel 
Ghibutiu, president of Romania's Chamber of Commerce and 
Industry, with the leadership of the National Confederation of 
Private Employers Institutions, which stipulates the setting up 
of a collaboration committee and envisages Peruvian economic 
missions to Romania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

