<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havana Notes Dismissal of Election Meddling Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Havana Notes Dismissal of Election Meddling Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1905125794 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1905125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Panamanian foreign ministry has dismissed a 
deputy's charges that the Cuban Government intervened in the 
electoral campaign to favor the opposition, the Democratic 
Revolutionary Party [PRD], which won the 8 May elections. A week 
before the elections, Leo Gonzalez, a deputy from the 
Nationalist Republican Liberal Movement, presented a series of 
documents to the Panamanian foreign ministry allegedly revealing 
that the Cuban Government had provided support and technical 
advice to Ernesto Perez' electoral campaign, which will put the 
PRD at the helm of the nation on 1 September. 
  The foreign ministry reached the conclusion that the 
documents are a forgery; it therefore closed the investigation 
and dismissed the information revealed by the deputy. 
  Miguel Martinez, Cuban charge d'affaires in Panama, said he 
had affirmed from the beginning that the documents were forged 
and that he was confident that the Panamanian foreign ministry 
would handle the issue carefully. 

</TEXT>

