<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Binational Agency Established With Argentina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Binational Agency Established With Argentina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1705152394 Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish 13 May 94 p 39 </F>
<F P=103> PY1705152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo LA MANANA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Daniel Rondan in Mercedes] </F>
  [Excerpt] Argentine Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella has 
announced the establishment of an organization for the 
development of our region. CODEFRO [expansion unknown] will be 
established as a binational agency within six weeks. The 
municipalities on the Uruguay River will join the foreign 
ministries. 
  Foreign Minister Di Tella on 11 May told the Uruguay River 
mayors that within six weeks the CODEFRO binational agency will 
be established under an agreement with the Argentine Government. 
  The Argentine and Uruguayan municipalities will play a very 
important political and technical role in this organization, 
because they, along with the foreign ministries, will be 
executive committee members. 
  The CODEFRO project, sponsored by the Inter-American 
Development Bank, will therefore be implemented. It represents 
the crowning of two years of work by the Planning and 
Negotiations Committee, which represents five Uruguayan 
municipalities and seven Argentine municipalities. It also 
represents a pilot project in Latin America in the field of 
regional integration, and a subsystem within Mercosur [Common 
Market of the South] planning. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

