Pastor, 47, who is considered a specialist in Latin American 
affairs. Ambassador Deane Hinton, who retired in 1993, was 
appointed in the aftermath of the 1989 U.S. invasion that 
overthrew General Manuel Antonio Noriega. U.S. Charge 
d'Affaires Oliver Garza temporarily replaced Hinton. 

