<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daniel Ortega: FSLN Grassroots Must Define Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daniel Ortega: FSLN Grassroots Must Define Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1905225494 Managua BARRICADA in Spanish 19 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PA1905225494 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua BARRICADA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Tatiana Rothschild] </F>
  [Text] Juigalpa, Chontales -- Here in a meeting with 
congressmen and guests of the extraordinary congress that will 
take place this weekend in Managua, Commander Daniel Ortega 
Saavedra said that "the FSLN [Sandinist National Liberation 
Front] candidate who emerges from the consensus is going to be 
the unity candidate." Ortega confirmed to Chontales Department 
congressmen his pledge to "respect the congress results even if 
they do not agree with the positions we are defending from the 
rank and file." 
  Ortega regretted having to compete for the post of secretary 
general with Commander Henry Ruiz and considered that those who 
try to run down or alter the principles that have guided the 
FSLN are gaining from the conflict. The current FSLN secretary 
general recognized Commander Ruiz as the revolutionary leader 
who historically has maintained leftist positions and expressed 
surprise that those who lean toward social democracy have taken 
shelter under Ruiz' candidacy. Ortega said "any Sandinist can 
have this aspiration, but the grassroots, who demand unity 
around popular struggles, must be the ones to define the party 
we want." 
  Peasant leader Celestino Garcia demanded it be noted clearly 
on the record that the launching of Commander Henry Ruiz' 
candidacy by Chontales Department Political Secretary Luis 
Enrique Figueroa was in Figueroa's capacity as a Sandinist 
follower. 
  Benedicto Miranda, Sandinist Youth department coordinator, 
questioned the role of journalists, who have assumed the task of 
deepening the trends rather than highlighting the party's 
platform program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

