<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Civil Defense Note on Eastern Provinces Flooding </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civil Defense Note on Eastern Provinces Flooding </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2005185894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2005185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Civil Defense General Staff announces 
that, as a result of the rainfall in the eastern provinces, 
which intensified yesterday, rivers and streams have risen and 
are flooding low areas. According to information received at 
1100 GMT on 20 May, the Provincial Defense Councils of Santiago 
de Cuba, Granma, and Guantanamo remain alert, as do a number of 
municipal and area defense councils in the eastern provinces. 
  As of this hour, 5,468 people have been evacuated to the 
homes of friends and relatives and 343 people are in shelters. 
Also, 6,540 animals have been moved to safer areas. Thirty-four 
houses were completely destroyed and another 300 are partially 
damaged. 
  In Taguasco Municipality, Sancti Spiritus Province, five 
houses were partially damaged by the intense rainfall. The 
damage to crops has yet to be evaluated. No loss of human life 
has been reported. Flood gates of some dams in this territory 
have been opened. 
  The National Civil Defense General Staff reminds the 
population in the affected provinces of the need to keep abreast 
of the situation through the weather forecasts and to comply 
with the measures taken by the defense councils in each 
territory. 

</TEXT>

