  [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the FAR, 
met with officers of the Arc Gloria, flagship of the Colombian 
Navy, who are visiting our country. Raul, who is also second 
secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba [PCC], spoke of his 
visit on board the Arc Gloria in 1976 and thanked the officers 
for stopping in Cuba for the second time. Raul was interested in 
learning of their activities during their few days in Cuba and 
saluted the recently appointed military-naval delegate from 
Colombia. 
  Colombian Ambassador Ricardo Santamaria, and the ship's 
Captain Eduardo Otero Erazo, as well as other officers and 
diplomats of the Colombian Navy, were present at the meeting. On 
the Cuban side, Division General Ulises Rosales del Toro, first 
vice minister of the Minfar [Ministry of the Revolutionary Armed 
Forces] and head of the General Staff, as well as other Minfar 
officials were also present at the meeting. 

