<H3> <TI>   Balaguer Declared Winner of Dominican Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Balaguer Declared Winner of Dominican Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2105020894 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2105020894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the conclusion of the vote count, the Central 
Electoral Commission of the Dominican Republic declared 
President Joaquin Balaguer the winner of the elections held on 
Monday [16 May.] In the final provisional bulletin, Balaguer 
maintained a one- point margin over Jose Francisco Pena Gomez, 
who demanded the annulment of the elections due to reported 
frauds. 
  Today, THE NEW YORK TIMES commented that the international 
community should not recognize President Balaguer's victory if 
it is the result of electoral fraud, as credible sources have 
indicated. THE NEW YORK TIMES pointed out that Balaguer was also 
accused of committing fraud in 1990's general elections, which 
confirmed him as president of that nation for another term. 

</TEXT>

