<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 19 May, PRC Ambassador Xu Yicong visited the 
Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology Center in Camaguey City. 
Center director Armando Moran informed Xu Yicong of the 
achievements in the production of veterinary medicines and in 
genetic and plant modifications. 
  During his visit, Xu was accompanied by Julian Rizo, first 
secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Camaguey, and by 
(Edislaf Gonzalez), president of the provincial People's 
Government. Ambassador Xu expressed his thanks for the 
scientific briefing during his visit to Camaguey and stressed 
the importance of the cooperation agreement between Cuba and the 
PRC, which is currently going well and expected to increase. 

