<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Says Government To Subsidize Electricity Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Says Government To Subsidize Electricity Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2005223094 Guatemala City LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 18 May 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PA2005223094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City LA REPUBLICA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemalan President Ramiro de Leon Carpio yesterday 
said his government will subsidize the increase in the electric 
power rate, whenever it goes into effect following the 
recommendations of the Multi Sector Commission. 
  The report on the electricity sector recommended a new rate 
per kilowatt hour that the INDE [National Electricity Institute] 
sells to the EEGSA [Empresa Electrica de Guatemala, S.A. -- 
Guatemalan Electric Power Company]. This will lead to an 
increase when the new rates take effect. De Leon Carpio 
indicated that "I already have the report," adding that the 
Guatemalan people can be certain that he will analyze the report 
carefully with his advisers. 
  Nevertheless, he said "we will continue with the subsidy, as 
recommended." He said his government has a policy of 
subsidizing the direct customer and that "this policy will have 
to continue until it no longer can be maintaisned." 
  He said he is very aware of the country's situation so he 
does not want to economically harm the poorest people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

