<H3> <TI>   Chamber of Deputies Dismisses Ibsen Pinheiro </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chamber of Deputies Dismisses Ibsen Pinheiro </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1905123094 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1905123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Neither the intervention of the PMDB [Brazilian 
Democratic Movement Party] leadership, nor an appeal to 
congressional corporatism could free Deputy Ibsen Pinheiro from 
being dismissed by the Chamber of Deputies. 
  During a 12-hour session, former Chamber of Deputies 
President Pinheiro was stripped of his congressional mandate by 
a vote of 296 to 139; 24 lawmakers abstained. 
  The Federal Supreme Court [STF] turned down a request for a 
court injunction filed by Pinheiro, who wanted to suspend his 
trial at the Chamber of Deputies. 
  Justice Carlos Mario Veloso reported at his office that the 
investigations requested by Pinheiro could be conducted only 
during the trial. 
  Ibsen Pinheiro also wanted the STF to annul a decision by 
the 
Constitution and Justice Commission, which recommended his 
dismissal. 

</TEXT>

