<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Gaviria Undergoes Foot Surgery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Gaviria Undergoes Foot Surgery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2105232394 Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 20 May 
94 p 14A </F>

<F P=103> PA2105232394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Carlos Uribe, who successfully treated [soccer 
player] Pibe Valderrama's knee injury, operated on President 
Cesar Gaviria yesterday morning. 
  The Presidency Information and Press Secretariat reported 
Gaviria "is recovering from the surgery he underwent." 
  According to the medical report, "the surgery lasted one 
hour 
and 50 minutes, and it freed the posterior tibial nerve, which 
was restrained at the tarsus tunnel of his right foot. This is 
why the operation could be satisfactorily performed." 
  Presidency sources also reported the chief of state was 
hospitalized at 0630. One hour later, he was transferred to the 
operating room, where he underwent surgery until 0930. Gaviria 
remained unconscious until noon due to the anesthesia. 
  Dr. Uribe said the president remained under medical 
supervision all day yesterday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

