<F P=100> Mexico </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner: New Chiapas Plan in Offing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peace Commissioner: New Chiapas Plan in Offing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2105152094 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2105152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Juan Carlos Santoyo from the "ACIR Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Manuel Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in Chiapas State, met today with permanent 
members of the Chamber of Deputies' Congress Commission, who are 
helping with the investigations in connection with the Chiapas 
conflict. Camacho Solis made a very important announcement to 
several legislators who closely follow the talks. He said that 
in less than three weeks, a new plan to consolidate peace in 
Chiapas will be disclosed. Camacho Solis also said that right 
now the most important thing is continuing the dialogue, which 
he stressed is going well. 
  This meeting resulted in the issuance of a communique by the 
Senate and signed not only by [words indistinct] but by (Rubi), 
which says that right now legislators view the negotiations 
favorably. Nevertheless, they stress the need to implement this 
peace program as quickly as possible and establish the necessary 
mechanisms to ensure that peace is achieved. 

</TEXT>

