<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Relations Established With Oman Sultanate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomatic Relations Established With Oman Sultanate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2405021294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2405021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the Republic of Cuba and the Sultanate of 
Oman established diplomatic relations at the ambassadorial level 
for the purpose of continuing to work for the benefit of their 
respective countries and peoples. 
  Fernando Remirez de Estenoz, and Salim Bin-Muhammad 
al-Qusaybi, permanent representatives to the United Nations for 
Cuba and Oman respectively, signed the documents relating to 
that sovereign decision by the two countries during a simple 
ceremony held at UN headquarters in New York. During the 
ceremony, the representative of Oman described the moment as 
historic, adding that it would contribute to the prosperity of 
the two nations and peoples. Remirez, first vice minister of 
Foreign Relations, also agreed in describing this step as 
historic for the two states, governments, and peoples. 

</TEXT>

