<H3> <TI>   PRC Ambassador Visits Las Tunas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Ambassador Visits Las Tunas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2305151694 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2305151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PRC Ambassador to Cuba Xu Yicong began a two-day 
visit to Las Tunas Province on 22 May. Xu Yicong will witness 
firsthand the Revolution's accomplishments in the province. 
Julian Lopez, Central Committee member and provincial first 
secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba, and Fransico Grave de 
Peralta, provincial People's Government president, greeted Xu 
Yicong at the house in which Las Tunas patriot Vicente Garcia 
was born. During his stay in Las Tunas, Xu Yicong will visit 
places of historical interest as well as service and production 
centers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

