<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> CUBA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Damage Agriculture in Santiago de Cuba </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Damage Agriculture in Santiago de Cuba </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2405013394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1959 GMT 
23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2405013394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The rains that have fallen in Santiago de Cuba 
Province since 16 May have caused considerable agricultural 
damage. The sugar harvest has been completely paralyzed because 
of road conditions and flooding in the sugarcane fields. 
Meanwhile, other crops have also reported serious damage. 
  In Segundo Frente Municipality, 50,000 plantain plants, 
2,500 
coffee trees, a coffee plant nursery, and many caballerias of 
mixed vegetables have been lost. In the Julio Antonio Mella 
region, 50 caballerias of sugarcane are flooded. Provincial 
authorities estimate losses throughout the province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

