<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conacom Communique Calls for Solidarity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conacom Communique Calls for Solidarity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2305192994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2305192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Congress of Democratic Movements, 
Conacom, calls for solidarity among democrats for a return of 
constitutional order. In a communique, Conacom states that what 
is immediately necessary is the overthrow of the Jonassaint 
government; General Cedras' early retirement, respecting the 
signature he put to the Governors Island agreement; and the 
return of President Aristide as soon as possible. Among other 
strategic actions, Conacom suggests holding meetings between 
President Aristide and the representatives of democratic 
political organizations for the purpose of expediting the 
application of the Governors Island agreement; meetings between 
the sectors that signed the New York pact, for the purpose of 
studying the pact's clauses; and meetings between 
representatives of democratic political organizations and the 
nation's various social sectors with a view to obtaining these 
sectors' support for these initiatives. 
  Conacom firmly believes that applying those proposals 
courageously and without delay will allow us to spare the 
country a catastrophe, while guaranteeing a return to 
constitutional order, especially that of President Aristide, 
states this Conacom press release. 

</TEXT>

