<H3> <TI>   Cavallo Says Economic Plan `Not Weakened' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cavallo Says Economic Plan `Not Weakened' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2405030094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2332 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2405030094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 23 May (NA) -- Economy Minister 
Domingo Cavallo believes the recent cabinet crisis "has not 
weakened the economic plan," and he indicated that it would be 
better not to create the Security Secretariat "until the public 
has been given an appropriate explanation about what is planned." 
  Cavallo referred to the controversial topic of the so-called 
super secretariat at the end of a ceremony in which agreements 
were signed for supplying drinking water to several provincial 
localities with financing from international organizations. 
  "President Carlos Menem has given a lot of importance to the 
topic and it is he who will finally decide it," the minister 
said. 

</TEXT>

