<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daniel Ortega Reelected FSLN Secretary General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daniel Ortega Reelected FSLN Secretary General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2305154094 Paris AFP in Spanish 1456 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2305154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 23 May (AFP) -- Official sources have 
reported that today, at the conclusion of the Sandinist National 
Liberation Front [FSLN] Special Congress, former Nicaraguan 
President Daniel Ortega was reelected secretary general of his 
party for a new three-year period. 
  Ortega was able to secure the support of the majority of the 
"orthodox" sector of the FSLN for his proposal to maintain the 
party's traditional struggle politicies in opposition to the 
current endorsed by his election adversary, Henry Ruiz, a 
legendary Sandinist leader who represented the reformist sector 
of this political organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

