<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commander Tomas Borge Closes FSLN Special Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commander Tomas Borge Closes FSLN Special Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2305232694 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1513 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2305232694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Sandino </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Commander Tomas Borge to close the Sandinist </F>
National Liberation Front, FSLN, Special Congress at the Olof 
Palme Convention Center in Managua -- live] 
  [Text] [Words indistinct] shown by you during 76 hours of 
nearly uninterrupted work, with the efforts of support teams -- 
which have carried out their work unselfishly -- with the 
efforts of the Electoral Council -- which has worked virtually 
without rest just as we did -- [and with the efforts] of the 
entire personnel, the physicians, and others who helped us 
ensure that this Congress worked, and with the extreme 
discipline, mutual respect, and the joy that was present in this 
event. 
  I do not know how to reward you other than by expressing our 
affection, but perhaps the biggest reward that we could give you 
after these 76 hours, is to be brief now. Thus, I declare the 
FSLN Special Congress closed. [applause] 

</TEXT>

