<H3> <TI>   Lula's Candidacy Said To Cause Drop in Debt Papers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lula's Candidacy Said To Cause Drop in Debt Papers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2405022994 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 19 
May 94 Section 1 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> PY2405022994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 18 May in Santos (Sao Paulo State), Alcides 
Tapias, president of the Brazilian Federation of Banks 
(Febraban), said Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva's presidential 
candidacy "may be one of the factors that caused foreign debt 
certificates to drop." 
  These certificates, which were issued by the Brazilian 
Government, have a nominal value of $100. On 4 May, they were 
negotiated for $74 and on 17 May their value dropped further to 
$67. 
  Tapias could not forecast the position banks will adopt if 
the certificates' value continues to drop. He said he has no 
data on the amount of these certificates still in the hands of 
the national banks. 

</TEXT>

