<F P=103> PY2305165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 22 May (ABE) -- Today, Finance Minister 
Rubens Ricupero clarified his position regarding the PSDB 
[Brazilian Social Democracy Party]. "It was neither aggressive 
commentary nor political sociology," said Ricupero, who avoided 
repeating the criticism he made of the party. On 20 May in 
Porto Alegre, Ricupero said he was not campaigning for the PSDB 
because he is a critic of the PSDB, which he compared to "a gay 
who has not dared come out of the closet." 
  "I made a commentary in the hallway, but it was friendly," 
Ricupero said. This time he praised the PSDB cadres. According 
to him, Senator Mario Covas (PSDB-Sao Paulo) was the one who 
best interpreted his words. "I can only say that I made them in 
a friendly tone," he added. Ricupero recalled his comments 
often get out of proportion because he is a professor. 
"Professors tend to be dramatic." 

</TEXT>

