<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on New Directorate, Robaina's Travel Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on New Directorate, Robaina's Travel Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2405191594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2405191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new Directorate for Affairs of Cubans Residing 
Abroad [Direccion para los Asuntos de los Cubanos Residentes en 
el Exterior] has been created at the Foreign Ministry. The 
creation of the directorate was announced on 24 May by Foreign 
Ministry spokesman Miguel Alfonso, who pointed out that the 
decision of the Cuban Government to create this directorate, 
directly subordinate to the minister's office, is part of the 
accords made in the recent conference, The Nation and the Emigre 
Community: 
  [Begin Alfonso recording] The characteristics of this new 
directorate are: First, it is directly subordinate to the 
foreign minister. As its name -- Directorate for Affairs of 
Cubans Residing Abroad -- indicates, the goal is to harmonize 
and coordinate an entire series of problems facing the emigre 
community and the solutions to those problems. [end recording] 
  The Foreign Ministry spokesman also announced that Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina will travel to Cairo to participate in 
the ministerial conference of the Nonaligned Movement from 31 
May to 3 June. Later, Robaina will make an official trip to 
Qatar to inaugurate the Cuban Embassy. 
  Alfonso added that in coming months, Cuba will participate 
in 
the Fourth Ibero-American Summit in Cartagena de Indias on 12-15 
June, and the assembly that will establish the Association of 
Caribbean States in Barbados. 

</TEXT>

