<H3> <TI>   Alarcon Visits Parliament, Meets With Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alarcon Visits Parliament, Meets With Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2405194694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2405194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, president of the 
National Assembly of the People's Government [ANPP], has visited 
the British Parliament at Westminster Palace. Alarcon's tour of 
the historic building was the first activity in the Cuban 
delegation's official visit at the invitation of the British 
Parliamentary Union group. The Cuban delegation received a 
detailed explanation of the Parliament's procedures, followed by 
a luncheon hosted by MP William Rogers, Labor Party spokesman 
for foreign affairs. The Cuban delegation also visited the 
famous Tate Gallery, where valuable works by artists of the UK 
are exhibited. 
  Alarcon also met with Don Arnold, member of the Conservative 
Party and treasurer of the Cuban-British group of the House of 
Commons, and Michael Marshall, president of the British 
Interparliamentary Council. Alarcon attended a welcome dinner 
hosted by John Ward, president of the British group, U.P. 
[expansion unknown] 
  According to sources from the Cuban Embassy in London, the 
ANPP delegation, on the first day of their visit, received 
expressions of satisfaction from the hosts and were pleased by 
the interest in learning the structure and function of the ANPP. 

</TEXT>

