Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits Havana Youth Labor Army Farms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits Havana Youth Labor Army Farms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2505121494 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2505121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces, visited three Youth Labor Army [EJT] 
integrated farms dedicated to miscellaneous crops and located in 
Altemisa and Alquizar Municipalities. Raul conversed with 
farmers who make up the EJT forces and showed interest in the 
work they do, their enthusiasm, and living conditions. The farm 
leadership briefed Raul and his delegation on the progress in 
achieving production goals and on the farm's efficiency, 
profitability, and costs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

